@page "/pdxMagicjam"

<PageTitle>PDX Magic Jam</PageTitle>

<main class="pmj-page">
    <section class="pmj-hero">
        <p class="pmj-kicker">Annual Magician's Convention</p>
        <h1>Portland Magic Jam</h1>
        <p class="pmj-date-location">March 13-15, 2026 | Portland, Oregon</p>
        <p class="pmj-lead">
            Another great magic weekend wrapped up to great reviews. The PMJ keeps reaching new levels of awesome,
            with top-tier talent and an intimate format built for learning, sharing, and community.
        </p>
        <div class="pmj-actions">
            <a class="pmj-btn pmj-btn-primary" href="https://pdxmagicjam.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Visit Official PMJ Site</a>
            <a class="pmj-btn pmj-btn-secondary" href="https://stats.sender.net/forms/e9rA3x/view" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Get Event Updates</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pmj-section">
        <h2>What a lineup</h2>
        <div class="pmj-grid">
            <article class="pmj-card">
                <h3>Featured 2026 Highlights</h3>
                <p>Silly Billy's kid show and post-show analysis, plus strong close-up and lecture sessions from Daniel Garcia and John Shryock.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="pmj-card">
                <h3>Legendary Performers</h3>
                <p>Richard Turner delivered a rare live card manipulation showcase, and Paul Draper brought both entertainment and education.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="pmj-card">
                <h3>Community + Contest</h3>
                <p>Over 100 magicians join each year. The 2026 contest winner was Charles Schneider.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pmj-section">
        <h2>Event history and overview</h2>
        <p>
            Started in 2009, PMJ is an annual 3-day convention welcoming magicians from Oregon, Washington, and beyond.
            It is open to beginners, hobbyists, and seasoned pros.
        </p>
        <p>
            The weekend includes instructional lectures, evening shows, dealers, panel discussions, contests,
            and plenty of face-time interaction with headliners.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pmj-section">
        <h2>Recent headliner snapshots</h2>
        <ul class="pmj-list">
            <li><strong>2025:</strong> Erik Tait, John Guastaferro, Jon Armstrong, Eric Jones</li>
            <li><strong>2023:</strong> Joshua Jay, Andi Gladwin, Carisa Hendrix, John Carney</li>
            <li><strong>2022:</strong> Dan Sperry, Stephen Bargatze, Jason Ladanye, Gregory Wilson</li>
            <li><strong>2020 (virtual):</strong> Max Maven, Shawn Farquhar, Stephen Bargatze, John Shryock</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="pmj-section">
        <h2>Register and contact</h2>
        <p>
            Explore full details on schedule, headliners, venue and hotel, workshops, evening shows,
            and registration directly on the official site.
        </p>
        <p>
            Questions: contact event organizer Greg Moreland via the contact options listed on the PMJ website.
        </p>
    </section>
</main>
